1. Full TCP Port Scan
sudo nmap -Pn -p- -T4 <TARGET_IP>
Purpose: Discover all open TCP ports on the target.
-Pn: Skip ping, assume target is online.
-p-: Scan all 65535 TCP ports.
-T4: Faster execution.

2. SYN Scan + Service Version + OS Detection
sudo nmap -sS -sV -O --osscan-guess -p- -T4 <TARGET_IP>
Purpose: Identify open ports stealthily, detect running services, versions, and OS.
-sS: Stealth SYN scan.
-sV: Detect service/version.
-O: Detect OS.
--osscan-guess: Make best guess if OS uncertain.
-p- & -T4: Scan all ports quickly.

3. UDP Scan (Targeted)
sudo nmap -sU -p 53,67,68,69,123,161 -T3 <TARGET_IP>
Purpose: Check common UDP services like DNS, DHCP, NTP.
-sU: Scan UDP ports.
-p: Target specific common UDP ports.
-T3: Moderate speed for reliability.

4. Detailed Service Version Detection
sudo nmap -sV --version-intensity 5 -p <comma-separated open ports> <TARGET_IP>
Purpose: Get detailed service/version info on specific ports.
--version-intensity 5: Maximum detection intensity.
